## Query keys (`lib/query-keys.ts`)

```ts
export const queryKeys = {
  auth: { me: ['auth', 'me'] as const },
  setup: {
    all: ['setup'] as const,
    status: ['setup', 'status'] as const,
    step: (n: number) => ['setup', 'step', n] as const,
  },
  settings: {
    all: ['settings'] as const,
    businessProfile: ['settings', 'business-profile'] as const,
    roundSettings: ['settings', 'round-settings'] as const,
    payment: ['settings', 'payment'] as const,
    services: ['settings', 'services'] as const,
    serviceAreas: ['settings', 'service-areas'] as const,
    technicians: ['settings', 'technicians'] as const,
    messageTemplates: ['settings', 'message-templates'] as const,
  },
} as const;

export function invalidateBusinessSettings(qc: QueryClient) {
  return Promise.all([
    qc.invalidateQueries({ queryKey: queryKeys.settings.businessProfile }),
    qc.invalidateQueries({ queryKey: queryKeys.settings.roundSettings }),
    qc.invalidateQueries({ queryKey: queryKeys.settings.payment }),
  ]);
}
```

Business Profile, Round Settings, and Payment share one `BusinessSettings` row — after ANY of the three PATCHes, always call `invalidateBusinessSettings`.

## API endpoints (build `*.api.ts` from this table + `/docs`)

Base: `{VITE_API_URL}`. Headers: `Content-Type: application/json`, `Authorization: Bearer <token>`. `GET` = ADMIN/MANAGER/TECHNICIAN; mutations = ADMIN/MANAGER only (403 else). Error body: `{ "error": string }` (no `code`/`fields` yet — build both coded + fallback paths).

### Setup (`setup.api.ts`) — only while `setupCompleted === false` except GETs + `/setup/complete`

| Method | Path | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| GET | `/setup/status` | Gate + stepper; use QueryClient defaults (no focus refetch — invalidate after mutations) |
| GET/POST | `/setup/step/1` | Business Profile; POST requires `businessName` |
| GET/POST | `/setup/step/2` | Payment; completes when `paymentRule` set |
| GET/POST | `/setup/step/3` | **Bulk replace** services — confirm dialog |
| GET/POST | `/setup/step/4` | Round Settings; `defaultCycleLength` required |
| GET/POST | `/setup/step/5` | Deferred stub — no DB write |
| GET/POST | `/setup/step/6` | Replace **pending-only** technicians — NOT full bulk replace |
| GET/POST | `/setup/step/7` | **Bulk replace** service areas — confirm dialog |
| GET/POST | `/setup/step/8` | **Upsert** ACTIVE round |
| GET/POST | `/setup/step/9` | **Additive** property bundle (201 on POST) |
| GET/POST | `/setup/step/10` | Per-round technician assignments |
| GET/POST | `/setup/step/11` | Generate SCHEDULED visits (call once) |
| GET | `/setup/step/12` | Review checklist only — no POST |
| POST | `/setup/complete` | **Await** `setup.status` invalidate before navigate |

### Settings (`settings.api.ts`) — only while `setupCompleted === true`

Singleton PATCHes: business-profile, round-settings, payment. Collections: services, service-areas, technicians (CRUD). Payment connect: `POST /settings/payment/:provider/connect` separate from rules PATCH. Message templates: deferred stub only. `GET /auth/me` in `auth.api.ts`.

### Invalidation map

| Mutation | Invalidate |
|---|---|
| `POST /setup/step/:n` | `setup.status` + `setup.step(n)` |
| `POST /setup/complete` | `setup.status` (await, then navigate) |
| PATCH business-profile / round-settings / payment / connect | `invalidateBusinessSettings(qc)` |
| Services CRUD | `settings.services` |
| Service areas CRUD | `settings.serviceAreas` |
| Technicians CRUD/deactivate | `settings.technicians` |

## QueryClient config

- Default: `staleTime: 30_000`, `refetchOnWindowFocus: false`, retry 4xx never / 5xx+network up to 2, `mutations.retry: 0`
- Global mutation error → toast except 400 (form) and `meta.silenceGlobalError`
- Default query options only — do not special-case `setup.status` with focus refetch

## `api/client.ts`

- Single-flight 401 refresh via Supabase → retry once → sign out on failure
- Forward `AbortSignal` from Query `queryFn`
- 204 → `undefined`; non-OK → `ApiError(status, message, code?, fields?)`

## Error handling

| Status | Behavior |
|---|---|
| 401 | Refresh + retry once in client |
| 403 | `handleForbidden` by `error.code` if present; legacy fallback for TECHNICIAN toast vs navigate |
| 400 | `setError` per field or root — never toast |
| 404 | Invalidate list, inline "no longer exists", close modal |
| 409 | Specific inline message; list intact |
| 5xx/network | Toast (mutations) or inline retry (queries) |

**BACKEND-GAP:** Live errors are `{ error: string }` only until `code`/`fields` ship.

## Form pattern

```ts
const form = useForm({
  resolver: zodResolver(schema),
  values: data ? toFormValues(data) : undefined,
  resetOptions: { keepDirtyValues: true },
});
```

Never `useEffect(() => reset(data))`. Unsaved-changes guard when `isDirty`. Skeleton while pending; inline retry on error.

## Bootstrap gate

1. Supabase session ready
2. `useSetupStatus` + `useMe`
3. Pending → full-screen loader
4. `setupCompleted === false` → `/setup`
5. `setupCompleted === true` → app + settings
6. TECHNICIAN → read-only settings UI

All settings queries: `enabled: status?.setupCompleted === true`.

## Wizard rules

12 steps: 1 Business Profile, 2 Payment, 3 Services, 4 Round Settings, 5 SMS stub, 6 Technicians, 7 Service Areas, 8 First Round, 9 Add Property (additive), 10 Assign Technicians, 11 Generate Visits, 12 Review & Launch.

- URL step source; clamp to `maxAllowedStep` from status
- Bulk-replace confirm: steps **3 and 7 only** ("replaces all current items")
- Step 6: pending invites only — accurate copy, preserve accepted techs
- Step 9: each POST creates one property bundle; Continue advances without re-POST
- Step 10: per-round technician replace; every ACTIVE round needs ≥ 1 tech
- Step 11: generate visits once (`startDate` today+, `cycleWeeks` 1–52)
- Step 12: GET checklist only; Launch = `POST /setup/complete` when `allRequiredComplete`
- Complete enabled only when `allRequiredComplete === true`

## Settings rules

- `defaultWorkingDays` editable **only** on Round Settings
- Payment rules PATCH ≠ provider connect mutation
- Service areas: disable delete when `linkedRounds.count > 0`; `isDefault` superRefine client-side
- Technicians: `displayName` + derived `appStatus`; accepted → `PATCH { active: false }`, never DELETE
- SMS templates: read-only stub
- Do not build UI for `bankDetails` until specified

## Money transforms (form layer only)

- `defaultPrice`: send `number`, receive `string`; Zod `z.coerce.number().positive()`
- `defaultCycleLength`: UI weeks → wire days `7|14|21|28|null`

## Zustand (`stores/ui.store.ts` only)

Modal state + toast queue. No lists, settings, tokens, or step index.

## Build order

1. Foundation (errors, client, types.gen, query-keys, QueryProvider, ui.store)
2. Gate (auth, setup status, bootstrap, role)
3. Wizard (shell → steps 1–8 → complete)
4. Settings (all sections)
5. Polish (skeletons, guards, devtools, dead-code sweep)

## Definition of done (self-verify)

- `tsc --noEmit` clean; no `any` on API boundaries
- `fetch(` only in `api/client.ts`
- No inline query keys; no server data in Zustand
- Double-click = one request; dirty forms survive focus refetch
- TECHNICIAN: no mutations; 403 → permission toast not /setup redirect
- URL step clamp; Complete awaits invalidate; step 8 gates Complete
- Step 6 re-save preserves accepted technicians
- Invalidation map honored; 400/404/409 behaviors correct
- Working days on Round Settings only; step 5 stub never blocks Complete

